TITLE: Testing event-based interface with assert.verifySteps()
DESCRIPTION: Example of using verifySteps() to test a WordFinder class that emits events. The test captures events using step() and verifies their order with verifySteps().
SOURCE: https://github.com/qunitjs/qunit/blob/main/docs/api/assert/verifySteps.md#2025-04-12_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
QUnit.test('good example', function (assert) {
  const finder = new WordFinder();
  finder.on('start', () => {
    assert.step('start');
  });
  finder.on('data', (word) => {
    assert.step(word);
  });
  finder.on('end', () => {
    assert.step('end');
  });
  finder.on('error', (e) => {
    assert.step('error: ' + e);
  });

  finder.process('Hello, 3.1. Great!');

  assert.verifySteps(['start', 'Hello', 'Great', 'end']);
});
```

