TITLE: Testing async voice service with assert.verifySteps()
DESCRIPTION: Example of using verifySteps() with async/await to test a voice service that emits events. The test captures noun events and verifies their order after awaiting the operation.
SOURCE: https://github.com/qunitjs/qunit/blob/main/docs/api/assert/verifySteps.md#2025-04-12_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
QUnit.test('good example', async function (assert) {
  MyVoice.on('noun', (word) => {
    assert.step(word);
  });
  const song = await MyVoice.sing('My Favorite Things', { lines: 1 });

  assert.true(song.finished, 'finished');
  assert.verifySteps([
    'Raindrops',
    'roses',
    'whiskers',
    'kittens'
  ]);
});
```

