TITLE: Testing Async Error Rejection with assert.rejects() in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates how to use assert.rejects() to test if an async function throws a specific error when given certain input.
SOURCE: https://github.com/qunitjs/qunit/blob/main/docs/api/assert/rejects.md#2025-04-12_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
async function feedBaby (food) {
  if (food === 'sprouts') {
    throw new RangeError('Do not like');
  }
  return true;
}

QUnit.test('example', async function (assert) {
  await assert.rejects(
    feedBaby('sprouts'),
    RangeError
  );
});
```

