TITLE: Asynchronous Hooks in QUnit Modules
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to use asynchronous hooks in QUnit modules. This example demonstrates connecting and disconnecting from a database before and after running tests in a module.
SOURCE: https://github.com/qunitjs/qunit/blob/main/docs/api/QUnit/module.md#2025-04-12_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
QUnit.module('Database connection', function (hooks) {
  hooks.before(async function () {
    await MyDb.connect();
  });

  hooks.after(async function () {
    await MyDb.disconnect();
  });

  // define tests...
});
```

