TITLE: Failing Example of Type Mismatch with deepEqual in QUnit JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates a common case where assert.deepEqual() fails due to type differences. The test compares objects with identical structure but with a property that has different types (number vs string), showing that deepEqual requires strict type equality.
SOURCE: https://github.com/qunitjs/qunit/blob/main/docs/api/assert/deepEqual.md#2025-04-12_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
QUnit.test('failing example', function (assert) {
  const result = {
    a: 'Albert',
    b: 'Berta',
    num: 123
  };

  // fails ,because the number 123 is not strictly equal to the string "123".
  assert.deepEqual(result, {
    a: 'Albert',
    b: 'Berta',
    num: '123'
  });
  // Actual:
  //           num: 123
  // Expected:
  //           num: "123"
});
```

