TITLE: Using QUnit assert.true() Method
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates various uses of assert.true() including successful and failing assertions. The method checks if the provided value is strictly equal to boolean true. Shows examples with different data types like strings, numbers, booleans, and special values.
SOURCE: https://github.com/qunitjs/qunit/blob/main/docs/api/assert/true.md#2025-04-12_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
QUnit.test('example', function (assert) {
  // success
  assert.true(true, 'boolean true');

  // failure
  assert.true('foo', 'non-empty string');
  assert.true('', 'empty string');
  assert.true(0, 'number zero');
  assert.true(false, 'boolean false');
  assert.true(NaN, 'NaN value');
  assert.true(null, 'null value');
  assert.true(undefined, 'undefined value');
});
```

