TITLE: Setting Module Options in QUnit
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to set module options in QUnit, including hooks for before, beforeEach, afterEach, and after. These options allow for setting up and tearing down test environments.
SOURCE: https://github.com/qunitjs/qunit/blob/main/docs/api/QUnit/module.md#2025-04-12_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
QUnit.module('example', {
  before () {
    // once for all tests
  },
  beforeEach () {
    // before every test
  },
  afterEach () {
    // after every test
  },
  after () {
    // once after all tests are done
  }
});
```

