TITLE: Testing publish/subscribe system with assert.verifySteps()
DESCRIPTION: Example of using verifySteps() to verify the correct behavior of a publisher-subscriber system, including subscriber registration, message publishing, and unsubscription.
SOURCE: https://github.com/qunitjs/qunit/blob/main/docs/api/assert/verifySteps.md#2025-04-12_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
QUnit.test('good example', function (assert) {
  const publisher = new Publisher();

  const subscriber1 = (message) => assert.step(`Sub 1: ${message}`);
  const subscriber2 = (message) => assert.step(`Sub 2: ${message}`);

  publisher.subscribe(subscriber1);
  publisher.subscribe(subscriber2);
  publisher.publish('Hello!');

  publisher.unsubscribe(subscriber1);
  publisher.publish('World!');

  assert.verifySteps([
    'Sub 1: Hello!',
    'Sub 2: Hello!',
    'Sub 2: World!'
  ]);
});
```

