TITLE: Deep Array Formatter in QUnit
DESCRIPTION: Complex example showing how to implement a deep formatter for arrays with proper depth tracking and recursion handling.
SOURCE: https://github.com/qunitjs/qunit/blob/main/docs/api/extension/QUnit.dump.setParser.md#2025-04-12_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
QUnit.dump.setParser('array', function (arr, stack) {
  if (QUnit.config.maxDepth && QUnit.dump.depth > QUnit.config.maxDepth) {
    return '[object Array]';
  }

  QUnit.dump.up();

  let i = arr.length;
  const ret = new Array(i);
  while (i--) {
    ret[i] = QUnit.dump.parse(arr[i], undefined, stack);
  }

  QUnit.dump.down();

  return QUnit.dump.join('[', ret, ']');
  // Output:
  // 1. 'pre' text.
  // 2. for each value:
  //    - line break and inner indentation
  //    - value as-is
  //    - comma (if not last)
  // 3. line break and outer indentation (if any)
  // 4. 'post' text
  //
  // [
  //   "foo",
  //   "bar"
  // ]
});
```

