TITLE: Using Module Scope in QUnit 2
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates the use of module scope introduced in QUnit 1.20 for simpler sharing of variables and associating tests with modules.
SOURCE: https://github.com/qunitjs/qunit/blob/main/docs/upgrade-guide-2.x.md#2025-04-12_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
QUnit.module('router', function (hooks) {
  let router;

  hooks.beforeEach(() => {
    router = new Router();
  });
  hooks.afterEach(() => {
    router.destroy();
  });

  QUnit.test('add', function (assert) {
    assert.true(router.add('/about'));
  });
});
```

