TITLE: Bad example: Assertions inside event callbacks
DESCRIPTION: A warning example showing why placing assertions directly inside event callbacks is risky. This can lead to false positives if callbacks don't run or run out of order.
SOURCE: https://github.com/qunitjs/qunit/blob/main/docs/api/assert/verifySteps.md#2025-04-12_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
// WARNING: This is a BAD example
QUnit.test('bad example 1', async function (assert) {
  const finder = new WordFinder();
  finder.on('start', () => {
    assert.true(true, 'start');
  });
  finder.on('middle', () => {
    assert.true(true, 'middle');
  });
  finder.on('end', () => {
    assert.true(true, 'end');
  });
  finder.on('error', () => {
    assert.true(false, 'error');
  });

  await maker.process();
});
```

