TITLE: Demonstrating Error-Throwing Function in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: Example function that throws an error when the first parameter is undefined
SOURCE: https://github.com/qunitjs/qunit/blob/main/docs/upgrade-guide-2.x.md#2025-04-12_snippet_8

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
function add (a, b) {
  if (a === undefined) {
    throw new Error('This is an error');
  }
}
```
